sidebar.tutorialSidebar.category.Interna.message: This section details the modules required to cover the functionalities offered by WMS in the Internal environment, intended for the operations team. Here we describe the steps required to perform package receipt, customer management, inventory control and monitoring of orders generated by customers, among other functions.  If you have access to the internal version of WMS, read on to learn about the modules available and discover how this system helps streamline and automate operational processes.

sidebar.tutorialSidebar.category.Gestion.message: The modules needed to manage fundamental elements in flows such as 3PL or Fulfillment within each G Global warehouse, such as warehouse management, trays, totes, among others, are presented. If you want to learn more about how this management is done, read on to discover which modules are involved and how they are used in the daily operation of a warehouse.
